'''March 14''' is the 14th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Enryaku|ja|延暦|qq=|12=draft}} 19th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[800]] {{ill|April 11|ja|4月11日|qq=|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fuji-san|ja|富士山|qq=|12=draft}} erupted (the Enryaku eruption).
* [[Shōka]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1257]] {{ill|March 31|ja|3月31日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Kōgen|ja|康元|qq=|12=draft}} to [[Shōka]].
* {{ill|Genroku|ja|元禄|qq=|12=draft}} 14th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1701]] {{ill|April 21|ja|4月21日|qq=|12=draft}}) – At the Matsunorō corridor of Edo Castle, the lord of the Akō Domain, {{ill|Asano Nagamasa|ja|浅野長矩|qq=|12=draft}}, was fatally injured by high-Ranking retainers of {{ill|Yoshira Yoshinaga|ja|吉良義央|qq=|12=draft}}; Nagamasa committed seppuku on the same day (the incident known as the Akō Incident).
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The 【Goka Jō no Oneshimon】 (Five Articles of the Imperial Oath) were promulgated, and discussions regarding the surrender of Edo ensued between {{ill|Katsu Kaishū|ja|勝海舟|qq=|12=draft}} and {{ill|Saigō Takamori|ja|西郷隆盛|qq=|12=draft}}.

