|13=User:Immanuelle/Asano Nagamasa|qq=}}, was fatally injured by high-Ranking retainers of {{ill|Yoshira Yoshinaga|ja|吉良義央|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshira Yoshinaga|qq=}}; Nagamasa committed seppuku on the same day (the incident known as the Akō Incident). * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} [[1868]] {{ill|April 6|ja|4月6日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/April 6|qq=}}) – The 【Goka Jō no Oneshimon】 (Five Articles of the Imperial Oath) were promulgated, and discussions regarding the surrender of Edo ensued between {{ill|Katsu Kaishū|ja|勝海舟|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Katsu Kaishū|qq=}} and {{ill|Saigō Takamori|ja|西郷隆盛|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saigō Takamori|qq=}}.
