{{Not to be confused with|March 14}}<!--hatnote--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十四|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 14일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 14''' is the 14th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 19th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[800]] [[:en:April 11|April 11]]) – [[:en:Mount Fuji|Fuji-san]] erupted (the Enryaku eruption). * [[Shōka]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1257]] [[:en:March 31|March 31]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Kōgen|Kōgen]] to [[Shōka]]. * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1701]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – At the Matsunorō corridor of Edo Castle, the lord of the Akō Domain, [[:en:Asano Naganori|Asano Nagamasa]], was fatally injured by high-Ranking retainers of [[:en:Kira Yoshinaka|Yoshira Yoshinaga]]; Nagamasa committed seppuku on the same day (the incident known as the Akō Incident). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:April 6|April 6]]) – The 【Goka Jō no Oneshimon】 (Five Articles of the Imperial Oath) were promulgated, and discussions regarding the surrender of Edo ensued between [[:en:Katsu Kaishū|Katsu Kaishū]] and [[:en:Saigō Takamori|Saigō Takamori]].
== Births == * [[:en:Meiō|Meio]] 6th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1497]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Mōri Motonari|Mōri Motonari]], a military commander (died [[1571]]). * [[Bunka]] 6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1809]] [[:en:April 28|April 28]]) – [[:en:Shimazu Nariakira|Shimazu Nariakira]], the 11th lord of the Satsuma Domain (died [[1858]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1701]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – [[:en:Asano Naganori|Asano Nagamasa]], lord of the Akō Domain (born [[1667]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1789]] [[:en:April 9|April 9]]) – [[:en:Miura Baien|Miura Baien]], a thinker (born [[1723]]).
== Commemorations == == See Also == {{Lunar Calendar See Also|3|13|3|15|2|14|4|3|0314|qq=}}
