== Events == * [[:en:Enryaku|Enryaku]] 19th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:800|800]] [[:en:April 11|April 11]]) – [[:en:Mount Fuji|Fuji-san]] erupted (the Enryaku eruption). * [[Shōka]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1257|1257]] [[:en:March 31|March 31]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Kōgen|Kōgen]] to [[Shōka]]. * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1701|1701]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – At the Matsunorō corridor of Edo Castle, the lord of the Akō Domain, [[:en:Asano Naganori|Asano Nagamasa]], was fatally injured by high-Ranking retainers of [[:en:Kira Yoshinaka|Yoshira Yoshinaga]]; Nagamasa committed seppuku on the same day (the incident known as the Akō Incident). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:April 6|April 6]]) – The 【Goka Jō no Oneshimon】 (Five Articles of the Imperial Oath) were promulgated, and discussions regarding the surrender of Edo ensued between [[:en:Katsu Kaishū|Katsu Kaishū]] and [[:en:Saigō Takamori|Saigō Takamori]].
== Births == * [[:en:Meiō|Meio]] 6th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1497|1497]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – [[:en:Mōri Motonari|Mōri Motonari]], a military commander (died [[:en:1571|1571]]). * [[Bunka]] 6th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1809|1809]] [[:en:April 28|April 28]]) – [[:en:Shimazu Nariakira|Shimazu Nariakira]], the 11th lord of the Satsuma Domain (died [[:en:1858|1858]]).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 14th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1701|1701]] [[:en:April 21|April 21]]) – [[:en:Asano Naganori|Asano Nagamasa]], lord of the Akō Domain (born [[:en:1667|1667]]). * [[:en:Kansei|Kansei]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1789|1789]] [[:en:April 9|April 9]]) – [[:en:Miura Baien|Miura Baien]], a thinker (born [[:en:1723|1723]]).
